BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 2, IRNA -- The Bosnian Deputy Premier 
Edib Bukvic wrapped up his three-day official visit here Monday 
morning and was seen off by Vice-President for Legal Affairs 
'Atta'ollah Mohajerani. 
  Lauding the readiness of Iranian people for helping the 
Muslim people of Bosnia-Herzegovina, Bukvic described his talks 
with Iranian officials as positive. 
  In his visit he signed three memoranda of understanding in 
political, scientific, cultural and technical areas. 

